    [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Geometry and Topology "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                377,
                128,
                620,
                148
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Solve every problem. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                426,
                156,
                568,
                172
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 1. The topological space "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is obtained by gluing two tetrahedra as illustrated by the figure. There is a unique way to glue the faces of one tetrahedron to the other so that the arrows are matched. The resulting complex has 2 tetrahedra, 4 triangles, 2 edges and 1 vertex. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                109,
                191,
                883,
                241
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Show that ?? can not have the homotopy type of a compact manifold without boundary. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                250,
                712,
                266
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/1dcad16590d701da49d529ca0c5c5ca15cc5c79f8009620e6d8d236d0acc0986.jpg"
                },
                "image_caption": [],
                "image_footnote": []
            },
            "bbox": [
                313,
                272,
                480,
                381
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/e4a7113eed10b3cd0e2d8962fbb743b0a91bc5165d0c09d169d74b273f07abfa.jpg"
                },
                "image_caption": [],
                "image_footnote": []
            },
            "bbox": [
                521,
                272,
                684,
                381
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 2. Suppose "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( M , h )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a closed (i.e., compact without boundary) Riemannian manifold, and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "h"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a metric on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "M"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\sec ( h ) \\leq - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", where sec(ℎ) is the sectional curvature. Suppose "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Sigma"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a closed minimal surface with genus "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "g"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( M , h )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Show that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                109,
                401,
                883,
                450
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\operatorname {A r e a} (\\Sigma) \\leq 4 \\pi (g - 1).",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/88b51c60a6f8670ef41417757ccedea152833407a3740759d8633a7467f0b11b.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                421,
                453,
                571,
                468
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Remark: A minimal surface is an immersed surface with constant mean curvature 0. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                112,
                484,
                694,
                501
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 3. For any topological space "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X ,"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "-th symmetric product of ?? is the quotient of the Cartesian product "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( X ) ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "by the action of the symmetric group "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "S _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", which permutes the factors in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( X ) ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". This space is denoted by "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathsf { S P } ^ { n } ( X )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and the topology is the natural quotient topology induced from "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( X ) ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                520,
                883,
                571
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Show that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { S P } ^ { n } ( \\mathbf { C P } ^ { 1 } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is homeomorphic to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { C P } ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Here "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { C P } ^ { 1 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { C P } ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are equipped with the manifold topology. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                579,
                854,
                595
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 4. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "M"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a complete noncompact Riemannian manifold. "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "M"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is said to have the geodesic loops to infinity property if for any "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "[ { \\boldsymbol { \\alpha } } ] \\in \\pi _ { 1 } ( M )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and any compact subset "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "K \\subset M"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", there is a geodesic loop "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\beta \\subset M \\backslash K ,"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "such that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\beta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is homotopic to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\alpha"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                614,
                883,
                666
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Show that if a complete noncompact Riemannian manifold ?? does not have the geodesic loops to infinity property, then there is a line in the universal cover "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\smash { \\widetilde { M } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                674,
                882,
                708
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Remark: A line is a geodesic "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\gamma : ( - \\infty , \\infty ) \\to M"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "such that dist "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( \\gamma ( s ) , \\gamma ( t ) ) = | s - t | ;"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "; a geodesic loop is a curve "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\beta : [ 0 , 1 ] \\to M"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "that is a geodesic and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\beta ( 0 ) = \\beta ( 1 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                718,
                883,
                751
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 5. A topological space ?? is called an "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "H"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "-space if there exist "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "e \\in X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mu : X { \\times } X \\to X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "such that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mu ( e , e ) = e"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and the maps "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x \\to \\mu ( e , x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x \\to \\mu ( x , e )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are both homotopic to the identity map. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                770,
                883,
                804
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Show that the fundamental group of an H-space is Abelian. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Show that the sphere "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "S ^ { 2 0 2 2 }"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "is not an H-space. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                125,
                813,
                568,
                854
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Historic Remark: “H” was suggested by Jean-Pierre Serre in recognition of the contributions in Topology by Heinz Hopf. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                864,
                883,
                898
            ]
        },
        {
